{"type":"message","id":"1fd9210e","parentId":"74dff7e9","timestamp":"2026-02-28T00:07:53.349Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_01VqKh7gs9DyHd5k65CYpikZ","toolName":"cron","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"jobs\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"46d1ca32-0bd0-43f4-bfa9-3e9e385271cd\",\n      \"name\": \"MC Heartbeat Ping\",\n      \"description\": \"Pings MC heartbeat + syncs daily memory to Vault every 2 hours\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1771819658199,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1772236865041,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"cron\",\n        \"expr\": \"0 */2 * * *\",\n        \"staggerMs\": 60000\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"0. Auto-refresh Codex OAuth token (runs silently if not needed):\\npython3 /data/workspace/scripts/refresh_codex_token.py 2>&1\\n\\nDo these three things silently:\\n\\n1. Ping MC heartbeat:\\ncurl -s -X POST https://resilient-chinchilla-241.convex.site/api/heartbeat -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" -H \\\"Authorization: Bearer 232e4ddf7d69c31e01ad0fa0a61f70c29e4837ed018a153cce1a429842bb7cbc\\\" -d \\\"{\\\\\\\"agentId\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"molty\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"currentTask\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"Heartbeat check\\\\\\\"}\\\"\\n\\n2. Sync today memory to MC Vault:\\nTODAY=$(date +%Y-%m-%d)\\nMEMORY_FILE=\\\"/data/workspace/memory/${TODAY}.md\\\"\\nif [ -f \\\"$MEMORY_FILE\\\" ]; then\\n  JSON=$(python3 -c \\\"import json,sys; print(json.dumps({\\\\\\\"agentId\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"molty\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"date\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"$TODAY\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"title\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"Daily Memory — $TODAY\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\":sys.stdin.read(),\\\\\\\"source\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"memory/$TODAY.md\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"tags\\\\\\\":[\\\\\\\"daily\\\\\\\"]}))\\\" < \\\"$MEMORY_FILE\\\")\\n  curl -s -X POST https://resilient-chinchilla-241.convex.site/api/memory -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" -H \\\"Authorization: Bearer 232e4ddf7d69c31e01ad0fa0a61f70c29e4837ed018a153cce1a429842bb7cbc\\\" -d \\\"$JSON\\\"\\nfi\\n\\nIf both succeed, reply HEARTBEAT_OK. If either fails, report the error.\\n\\n3. Run Todoist↔MC completion sync:\\nbash /data/workspace/scripts/mc-todoist-sync-v2.sh 2>&1\",\n        \"model\": \"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5\"\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"none\",\n        \"channel\": \"last\",\n        \"bestEffort\": true\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1772244054211,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1772236854217,\n        \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 10824,\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 0,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDelivered\": false,\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"not-delivered\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"bdb28765-f508-4271-a04d-9408d39f49fd\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"name\": \"Daily Standup 5PM HKT\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1770276918859,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1772182850054,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"cron\",\n        \"expr\": \"0 9 * * *\",\n        \"tz\": \"UTC\"\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"Daily standup time (5PM HKT). Do these steps:\\\\n\\\\n0. Run Todoist↔MC sync first:\\nbash /data/workspace/scripts/mc-todoist-sync-v2.sh 2>&1\\n\\n1. Run the standup script:\\\\nbash -c 'cd /data/workspace && .venv/bin/python3 scripts/daily_standup.py 2>&1'\\\\n\\\\n2. Parse the output for: __PAGE_URL__, __TASK_COUNT__, __OVERDUE__, __TODAY__, __NEEDS_INPUT__, __TG_SUMMARY__\\\\n\\\\n3. Send a Telegram message to Guillermo (target: 1097408992, channel: telegram):\\\\n⏰ *Daily Standup — [day date]*\\\\n\\\\n📄 [PAGE_URL]\\\\n\\\\n*[TASK_COUNT] tasks · [OVERDUE] overdue · [TODAY] due today · [NEEDS_INPUT] need your call*\\\\n\\\\n[TG_SUMMARY]\\\\n\\\\nKeep it concise. If the script fails, still send a Telegram message with the error.\\n\\nIMPORTANT: The Telegram message must end with this exact line:\\n_Fill in the Action column for each task, then reply *standup done* when finished._\",\n        \"model\": \"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 180\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1772269200000,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1772182800009,\n        \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 50045,\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 0,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDelivered\": true,\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"delivered\"\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"d9da8767-0650-43f8-9c6b-420affb67c40\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"name\": \"Daily Backup (9 PM HKT)\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1771075774802,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1772197267409,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"cron\",\n        \"expr\": \"0 13 * * *\",\n        \"tz\": \"UTC\"\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"Run the daily backup:\\n\\n1. Run backup: bash /data/workspace/backups/backup.sh\\n2. Return result as plain text: backup size, success/fail.\\n\\nDo NOT run updates (handled by morning cron). Do NOT post to any channel; return plain text only.\",\n        \"model\": \"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 180\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\",\n        \"channel\": \"discord\",\n        \"to\": \"channel:1468164160398557216\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1772283600000,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1772197200010,\n        \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 67399,\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 0,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDelivered\": true,\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"delivered\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"c0705ffd-9c7f-4f90-839b-7f3a9d660371\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"name\": \"Fleet Update Check (05:15 HKT)\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1771119666523,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1772198104810,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"cron\",\n        \"expr\": \"15 21 * * *\",\n        \"tz\": \"Asia/Hong_Kong\"\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"Fleet OpenClaw release check. Run: /data/workspace/.venv/bin/python3 /data/workspace/scripts/check-openclaw-releases.py 2>&1\\n\\nIf exit 0 with no new version: reply HEARTBEAT_OK.\\n\\nIf an update ran (exit 0 or 1): read /data/workspace/state/fleet-update-report.json and:\\n1. Post a summary to Discord #command-center (channel 1468164160398557216) with: version, per-agent status, what's new (TMNT-relevant), and HOW the squad will use the new features — not just a feature list\\n2. Send the same summary to Guillermo on Telegram (target 1097408992) as a separate message\\n\\nIf the script itself failed to run: post the error to #command-center and Telegram.\",\n        \"model\": \"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 1800\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\",\n        \"channel\": \"discord\",\n        \"to\": \"channel:1468164181155909743\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1772284500000,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1772198100011,\n        \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 4799,\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 0,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDelivered\": false,\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"not-delivered\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"1146fab9-1674-44a3-98bc-22b0803bd165\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"name\": \"daily-log-compaction\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1770798643618,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1772204407681,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"cron\",\n        \"expr\": \"0 23 * * *\",\n        \"tz\": \"Asia/Hong_Kong\"\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"End-of-day memory compaction for Molty.\\n\\n1. Read today's daily log: /data/workspace/memory/2026-MM-DD.md (use today's date)\\n2. If it exceeds 10KB, create a summary version:\\n   - Keep key decisions, action items, lessons learned\\n   - Remove verbose tool outputs, repeated status checks, routine confirmations\\n   - Target: ~2-3KB summary\\n   - Save raw version to memory/archive/YYYY-MM-DD-raw.md\\n   - Replace daily file with summary\\n3. If under 10KB, no action needed — reply HEARTBEAT_OK\\n4. Check if any important items should be added to MEMORY.md (but respect the 15KB cap)\\n\\nDo NOT post to any channel; return plain text only.\",\n        \"model\": \"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 180\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"none\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1772290800000,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1772204400019,\n        \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 7662,\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 0,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDelivered\": false,\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"not-delivered\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"80105aa4-e6de-4cbb-ae8a-d9e75c84b3fa\",\n      \"name\": \"Molty Nightly Task Worker\",\n      \"description\": \"Executes Molty-owned Todoist tasks autonomously. Results logged for morning briefing.\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1771928556133,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1772215459986,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"cron\",\n        \"expr\": \"0 18 * * *\",\n        \"tz\": \"UTC\",\n        \"staggerMs\": 0\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"Nightly task worker — 02:00 HKT. Work through Molty-owned Todoist tasks silently and autonomously.\\n\\nTODAY=$(date +%Y-%m-%d)\\nLOG=\\\"/data/workspace/logs/overnight-tasks-${TODAY}.md\\\"\\n\\n1. Fetch active tasks from Molty's Den project:\\ncurl -s \\\"https://api.todoist.com/api/v1/tasks?project_id=6fwH32grqrCJF23R\\\" -H \\\"Authorization: Bearer 9a26743814658c9e82d92aa716b46a9b0a2257c4\\\"\\n\\n2. For each task, classify:\\n   - AUTO: research / write / draft / plan / compile / summarise / find → execute it\\n   - FLAG: needs Guillermo decision / external send / financial / ambiguous → log reason only\\n\\n3. For AUTO tasks — execute fully:\\n   - Research: web_search + web_fetch → write a Notion page with findings\\n   - Writing: produce the document as a Notion page\\n   - After completing: close in Todoist (POST /tasks/{id}/close with Bearer 9a26743814658c9e82d92aa716b46a9b0a2257c4)\\n   - Close in MC: PATCH https://resilient-chinchilla-241.convex.site/api/task with {\\\"id\\\":\\\"<mc_id>\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"done\\\"} Bearer 232e4ddf7d69c31e01ad0fa0a61f70c29e4837ed018a153cce1a429842bb7cbc\\n\\n4. Create Notion output pages as children of the most recent standup page when possible.\\n\\n5. Write log to /data/workspace/logs/overnight-tasks-${TODAY}.md:\\n   # Overnight Tasks — {DATE}\\n   ## ✅ Completed ({n})\\n   - Task name → Notion link (or \\\"no output\\\" if N/A)\\n   ## ⏭️ Flagged — needs input ({n})\\n   - Task name: reason why flagged\\n   ## ❌ Failed ({n})\\n   - Task name: error detail\\n\\n6. Commit the log: cd /data/workspace && git add logs/ && git commit -m \\\"log: overnight tasks ${TODAY}\\\"\\n\\nQuality over speed. If a task is complex, do it properly. If you cannot complete a task in this session, mark it in-progress in the log (do NOT close it in Todoist).\",\n        \"model\": \"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 1500\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\",\n        \"channel\": \"last\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1772301600000,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1772215200015,\n        \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 259971,\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 0,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDelivered\": true,\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"delivered\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"7906d2f7-ef74-481a-8aff-53ea44d32eee\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"name\": \"memory-size-guardrail\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1770798635243,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1772226120013,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"cron\",\n        \"expr\": \"0 5 * * *\",\n        \"tz\": \"Asia/Hong_Kong\"\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"Check workspace file sizes for context bloat. Run: wc -c /data/workspace/*.md /data/workspace/memory/*.md 2>/dev/null | sort -rn | head -15\\n\\nCaps: MEMORY.md ≤15KB, AGENTS.md ≤8KB, TOOLS.md ≤5KB, daily files ≤10KB each.\\n\\nIf ANY file exceeds its cap, return a summary with file name, current size, and cap.\\n\\nAlso: move any memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md files older than 7 days to memory/archive/.\\n\\nIf everything is under cap, reply HEARTBEAT_OK.\\n\\nDo NOT call the message tool. Return your summary as plain text only; the delivery system will post it.\",\n        \"model\": \"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 120,\n        \"text\": \"Check workspace file sizes for context bloat. Review: wc -c /data/workspace/*.md /data/workspace/memory/*.md 2>/dev/null | sort -rn | head -15\\n\\nMEMORY.md ≤15KB, AGENTS.md ≤8KB, TOOLS.md ≤5KB, daily files ≤10KB each. No action needed unless a file is close to its cap.\"\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\",\n        \"channel\": \"discord\",\n        \"to\": \"channel:1468164160398557216\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1772312400000,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1772226000009,\n        \"lastStatus\": \"error\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 120004,\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 8,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"error\",\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"unknown\",\n        \"lastError\": \"cron: job execution timed out\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"8b748f23-91d0-425d-9e4b-e7246e46ce8c\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"name\": \"Daily Morning Briefing (6AM HKT)\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1770354555841,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1772231400009,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"cron\",\n        \"expr\": \"30 6 * * *\",\n        \"tz\": \"Asia/Hong_Kong\"\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"main\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"next-heartbeat\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"systemEvent\",\n        \"text\": \"Morning briefing time. Run: /data/workspace/.venv/bin/python3 /data/workspace/scripts/morning_briefing.py 2>&1 | tee /data/workspace/PRIORITY_BRIEFING.md\\n\\nThen send the output to Guillermo on Telegram (target 1097408992). Send the actual briefing content, not a summary of it.\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1772317800000,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1772231400008,\n        \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 1,\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 0,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"not-requested\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"44fb9d22-a77a-4de1-9c09-5edef483264e\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"name\": \"weekly-para-curation\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1770180106367,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1771779606630,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"cron\",\n        \"expr\": \"0 1 * * 1\",\n        \"tz\": \"Asia/Hong_Kong\"\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"🗂️ WEEKLY PARA CURATION\\n\\nExecute the PARA curation script:\\n\\npython3 /data/workspace/scripts/para_curation.py 2>&1\\n\\nScript will:\\n1. Scan shared project directories\\n2. Archive files older than 1 year\\n3. Log migration details\\n4. Create a migration report\\n\\nCheck /data/workspace/logs/para_curation.log for details.\\n\\nDo NOT post to any channel; return plain text only.\",\n        \"model\": \"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 180\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1772384400000,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1771779600011,\n        \"lastStatus\": \"error\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 6619,\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 1,\n        \"lastError\": \"cron announce delivery failed\"\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\",\n        \"channel\": \"discord\",\n        \"to\": \"channel:1468164160398557216\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"f17da2d2-3b49-4be5-be9d-d29a27a8dbb9\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"name\": \"healthcheck:security-audit\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1770299752473,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1771786834028,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"cron\",\n        \"expr\": \"0 3 * * 1\",\n        \"tz\": \"Asia/Hong_Kong\"\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"next-heartbeat\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"Run a security audit: execute `openclaw security audit --deep` and `openclaw update status`. Compare results against the last audit. If any NEW findings appear (not previously accepted risks), return them clearly. Save results to memory/security-audit-latest.md. Accepted risks: dangerouslyDisableDeviceAuth=true, Sonnet 4 weak tier warning, Discord allowlist warning.\\n\\nDo NOT post to any channel; return plain text only. The delivery system handles routing.\",\n        \"model\": \"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 180\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1772391600000,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1771786800011,\n        \"lastStatus\": \"error\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 34017,\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 1,\n        \"lastError\": \"cron announce delivery failed\"\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\",\n        \"channel\": \"discord\",\n        \"to\": \"channel:1468164160398557216\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"3db9477e-5dee-4731-bfb4-9e0abfcbcab2\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"name\": \"Weekly Memory Health Check\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1771334751465,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1771817394142,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"cron\",\n        \"expr\": \"0 10 * * 1\",\n        \"tz\": \"Asia/Hong_Kong\"\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"Weekly memory health check. Return plain text only.\\n\\n1. Check the builtin memory index at /data/.openclaw/memory/main.sqlite: total files, vault files (path LIKE \\\"memory/vault/%\\\"), squad files (path LIKE \\\"memory/squad/%\\\"), total chunks, total embeddings.\\n\\n2. Canary test with RETRY — run memory_search for \\\"Guillermo\\\" (high-confidence query). If it returns 0 results, wait 10 seconds and retry with \\\"TMNT fleet\\\". Only report FAIL if BOTH attempts return 0 results. If first fails but second succeeds, report WARN (transient).\\n\\n3. Check disk usage: du -sh /data/workspace/memory/ and du -sh /data/.openclaw/memory/\\n\\n4. Confirm QMD is NOT installed (we removed it Feb 23, now using OpenAI embeddings). Flag if /usr/local/bin/qmd exists.\\n\\n5. Report summary: index counts, canary pass/warn/fail, disk usage, backend type.\\n\\nSeverity guide:\\n- Both canary queries fail = HIGH (search broken)\\n- First fails, retry succeeds = WARN (transient)\\n- Both succeed = OK\",\n        \"model\": \"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 120\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\",\n        \"to\": \"channel:1468164160398557216\",\n        \"bestEffort\": true\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1772416800000,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1771817380776,\n        \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 13366,\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 0\n      }\n    }\n  ],\n  \"total\": 11,\n  \"offset\": 0,\n  \"limit\": 11,\n  \"hasMore\": false,\n  \"nextOffset\": null\n}"}],"details":{"jobs":[{"id":"46d1ca32-0bd0-43f4-bfa9-3e9e385271cd","name":"MC Heartbeat Ping","description":"Pings MC heartbeat + syncs daily memory to Vault every 2 hours","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1771819658199,"updatedAtMs":1772236865041,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 */2 * * *","staggerMs":60000},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"0. Auto-refresh Codex OAuth token (runs silently if not needed):\npython3 /data/workspace/scripts/refresh_codex_token.py 2>&1\n\nDo these three things silently:\n\n1. Ping MC heartbeat:\ncurl -s -X POST https://resilient-chinchilla-241.convex.site/api/heartbeat -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -H \"Authorization: Bearer 232e4ddf7d69c31e01ad0fa0a61f70c29e4837ed018a153cce1a429842bb7cbc\" -d \"{\\\"agentId\\\":\\\"molty\\\",\\\"currentTask\\\":\\\"Heartbeat check\\\"}\"\n\n2. Sync today memory to MC Vault:\nTODAY=$(date +%Y-%m-%d)\nMEMORY_FILE=\"/data/workspace/memory/${TODAY}.md\"\nif [ -f \"$MEMORY_FILE\" ]; then\n  JSON=$(python3 -c \"import json,sys; print(json.dumps({\\\"agentId\\\":\\\"molty\\\",\\\"date\\\":\\\"$TODAY\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Daily Memory — $TODAY\\\",\\\"content\\\":sys.stdin.read(),\\\"source\\\":\\\"memory/$TODAY.md\\\",\\\"tags\\\":[\\\"daily\\\"]}))\" < \"$MEMORY_FILE\")\n  curl -s -X POST https://resilient-chinchilla-241.convex.site/api/memory -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -H \"Authorization: Bearer 232e4ddf7d69c31e01ad0fa0a61f70c29e4837ed018a153cce1a429842bb7cbc\" -d \"$JSON\"\nfi\n\nIf both succeed, reply HEARTBEAT_OK. If either fails, report the error.\n\n3. Run Todoist↔MC completion sync:\nbash /data/workspace/scripts/mc-todoist-sync-v2.sh 2>&1","model":"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5"},"delivery":{"mode":"none","channel":"last","bestEffort":true},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1772244054211,"lastRunAtMs":1772236854217,"lastStatus":"ok","lastDurationMs":10824,"consecutiveErrors":0,"lastRunStatus":"ok","lastDelivered":false,"lastDeliveryStatus":"not-delivered"}},{"id":"bdb28765-f508-4271-a04d-9408d39f49fd","agentId":"main","name":"Daily Standup 5PM HKT","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1770276918859,"updatedAtMs":1772182850054,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 9 * * *","tz":"UTC"},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"Daily standup time (5PM HKT). Do these steps:\\n\\n0. Run Todoist↔MC sync first:\nbash /data/workspace/scripts/mc-todoist-sync-v2.sh 2>&1\n\n1. Run the standup script:\\nbash -c 'cd /data/workspace && .venv/bin/python3 scripts/daily_standup.py 2>&1'\\n\\n2. Parse the output for: __PAGE_URL__, __TASK_COUNT__, __OVERDUE__, __TODAY__, __NEEDS_INPUT__, __TG_SUMMARY__\\n\\n3. Send a Telegram message to Guillermo (target: 1097408992, channel: telegram):\\n⏰ *Daily Standup — [day date]*\\n\\n📄 [PAGE_URL]\\n\\n*[TASK_COUNT] tasks · [OVERDUE] overdue · [TODAY] due today · [NEEDS_INPUT] need your call*\\n\\n[TG_SUMMARY]\\n\\nKeep it concise. If the script fails, still send a Telegram message with the error.\n\nIMPORTANT: The Telegram message must end with this exact line:\n_Fill in the Action column for each task, then reply *standup done* when finished._","model":"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5","timeoutSeconds":180},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1772269200000,"lastRunAtMs":1772182800009,"lastStatus":"ok","lastDurationMs":50045,"consecutiveErrors":0,"lastRunStatus":"ok","lastDelivered":true,"lastDeliveryStatus":"delivered"},"delivery":{"mode":"announce"}},{"id":"d9da8767-0650-43f8-9c6b-420affb67c40","agentId":"main","name":"Daily Backup (9 PM HKT)","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1771075774802,"updatedAtMs":1772197267409,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 13 * * *","tz":"UTC"},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"Run the daily backup:\n\n1. Run backup: bash /data/workspace/backups/backup.sh\n2. Return result as plain text: backup size, success/fail.\n\nDo NOT run updates (handled by morning cron). Do NOT post to any channel; return plain text only.","model":"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5","timeoutSeconds":180},"delivery":{"mode":"announce","channel":"discord","to":"channel:1468164160398557216"},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1772283600000,"lastRunAtMs":1772197200010,"lastStatus":"ok","lastDurationMs":67399,"consecutiveErrors":0,"lastRunStatus":"ok","lastDelivered":true,"lastDeliveryStatus":"delivered"}},{"id":"c0705ffd-9c7f-4f90-839b-7f3a9d660371","agentId":"main","name":"Fleet Update Check (05:15 HKT)","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1771119666523,"updatedAtMs":1772198104810,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"15 21 * * *","tz":"Asia/Hong_Kong"},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"Fleet OpenClaw release check. Run: /data/workspace/.venv/bin/python3 /data/workspace/scripts/check-openclaw-releases.py 2>&1\n\nIf exit 0 with no new version: reply HEARTBEAT_OK.\n\nIf an update ran (exit 0 or 1): read /data/workspace/state/fleet-update-report.json and:\n1. Post a summary to Discord #command-center (channel 1468164160398557216) with: version, per-agent status, what's new (TMNT-relevant), and HOW the squad will use the new features — not just a feature list\n2. Send the same summary to Guillermo on Telegram (target 1097408992) as a separate message\n\nIf the script itself failed to run: post the error to #command-center and Telegram.","model":"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5","timeoutSeconds":1800},"delivery":{"mode":"announce","channel":"discord","to":"channel:1468164181155909743"},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1772284500000,"lastRunAtMs":1772198100011,"lastStatus":"ok","lastDurationMs":4799,"consecutiveErrors":0,"lastRunStatus":"ok","lastDelivered":false,"lastDeliveryStatus":"not-delivered"}},{"id":"1146fab9-1674-44a3-98bc-22b0803bd165","agentId":"main","name":"daily-log-compaction","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1770798643618,"updatedAtMs":1772204407681,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 23 * * *","tz":"Asia/Hong_Kong"},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"End-of-day memory compaction for Molty.\n\n1. Read today's daily log: /data/workspace/memory/2026-MM-DD.md (use today's date)\n2. If it exceeds 10KB, create a summary version:\n   - Keep key decisions, action items, lessons learned\n   - Remove verbose tool outputs, repeated status checks, routine confirmations\n   - Target: ~2-3KB summary\n   - Save raw version to memory/archive/YYYY-MM-DD-raw.md\n   - Replace daily file with summary\n3. If under 10KB, no action needed — reply HEARTBEAT_OK\n4. Check if any important items should be added to MEMORY.md (but respect the 15KB cap)\n\nDo NOT post to any channel; return plain text only.","model":"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5","timeoutSeconds":180},"delivery":{"mode":"none"},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1772290800000,"lastRunAtMs":1772204400019,"lastStatus":"ok","lastDurationMs":7662,"consecutiveErrors":0,"lastRunStatus":"ok","lastDelivered":false,"lastDeliveryStatus":"not-delivered"}},{"id":"80105aa4-e6de-4cbb-ae8a-d9e75c84b3fa","name":"Molty Nightly Task Worker","description":"Executes Molty-owned Todoist tasks autonomously. Results logged for morning briefing.","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1771928556133,"updatedAtMs":1772215459986,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 18 * * *","tz":"UTC","staggerMs":0},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"Nightly task worker — 02:00 HKT. Work through Molty-owned Todoist tasks silently and autonomously.\n\nTODAY=$(date +%Y-%m-%d)\nLOG=\"/data/workspace/logs/overnight-tasks-${TODAY}.md\"\n\n1. Fetch active tasks from Molty's Den project:\ncurl -s \"https://api.todoist.com/api/v1/tasks?project_id=6fwH32grqrCJF23R\" -H \"Authorization: Bearer 9a26743814658c9e82d92aa716b46a9b0a2257c4\"\n\n2. For each task, classify:\n   - AUTO: research / write / draft / plan / compile / summarise / find → execute it\n   - FLAG: needs Guillermo decision / external send / financial / ambiguous → log reason only\n\n3. For AUTO tasks — execute fully:\n   - Research: web_search + web_fetch → write a Notion page with findings\n   - Writing: produce the document as a Notion page\n   - After completing: close in Todoist (POST /tasks/{id}/close with Bearer 9a26743814658c9e82d92aa716b46a9b0a2257c4)\n   - Close in MC: PATCH https://resilient-chinchilla-241.convex.site/api/task with {\"id\":\"<mc_id>\",\"status\":\"done\"} Bearer 232e4ddf7d69c31e01ad0fa0a61f70c29e4837ed018a153cce1a429842bb7cbc\n\n4. Create Notion output pages as children of the most recent standup page when possible.\n\n5. Write log to /data/workspace/logs/overnight-tasks-${TODAY}.md:\n   # Overnight Tasks — {DATE}\n   ## ✅ Completed ({n})\n   - Task name → Notion link (or \"no output\" if N/A)\n   ## ⏭️ Flagged — needs input ({n})\n   - Task name: reason why flagged\n   ## ❌ Failed ({n})\n   - Task name: error detail\n\n6. Commit the log: cd /data/workspace && git add logs/ && git commit -m \"log: overnight tasks ${TODAY}\"\n\nQuality over speed. If a task is complex, do it properly. If you cannot complete a task in this session, mark it in-progress in the log (do NOT close it in Todoist).","model":"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6","timeoutSeconds":1500},"delivery":{"mode":"announce","channel":"last"},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1772301600000,"lastRunAtMs":1772215200015,"lastStatus":"ok","lastDurationMs":259971,"consecutiveErrors":0,"lastRunStatus":"ok","lastDelivered":true,"lastDeliveryStatus":"delivered"}},{"id":"7906d2f7-ef74-481a-8aff-53ea44d32eee","agentId":"main","name":"memory-size-guardrail","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1770798635243,"updatedAtMs":1772226120013,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 5 * * *","tz":"Asia/Hong_Kong"},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"Check workspace file sizes for context bloat. Run: wc -c /data/workspace/*.md /data/workspace/memory/*.md 2>/dev/null | sort -rn | head -15\n\nCaps: MEMORY.md ≤15KB, AGENTS.md ≤8KB, TOOLS.md ≤5KB, daily files ≤10KB each.\n\nIf ANY file exceeds its cap, return a summary with file name, current size, and cap.\n\nAlso: move any memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md files older than 7 days to memory/archive/.\n\nIf everything is under cap, reply HEARTBEAT_OK.\n\nDo NOT call the message tool. Return your summary as plain text only; the delivery system will post it.","model":"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5","timeoutSeconds":120,"text":"Check workspace file sizes for context bloat. Review: wc -c /data/workspace/*.md /data/workspace/memory/*.md 2>/dev/null | sort -rn | head -15\n\nMEMORY.md ≤15KB, AGENTS.md ≤8KB, TOOLS.md ≤5KB, daily files ≤10KB each. No action needed unless a file is close to its cap."},"delivery":{"mode":"announce","channel":"discord","to":"channel:1468164160398557216"},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1772312400000,"lastRunAtMs":1772226000009,"lastStatus":"error","lastDurationMs":120004,"consecutiveErrors":8,"lastRunStatus":"error","lastDeliveryStatus":"unknown","lastError":"cron: job execution timed out"}},{"id":"8b748f23-91d0-425d-9e4b-e7246e46ce8c","agentId":"main","name":"Daily Morning Briefing (6AM HKT)","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1770354555841,"updatedAtMs":1772231400009,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"30 6 * * *","tz":"Asia/Hong_Kong"},"sessionTarget":"main","wakeMode":"next-heartbeat","payload":{"kind":"systemEvent","text":"Morning briefing time. Run: /data/workspace/.venv/bin/python3 /data/workspace/scripts/morning_briefing.py 2>&1 | tee /data/workspace/PRIORITY_BRIEFING.md\n\nThen send the output to Guillermo on Telegram (target 1097408992). Send the actual briefing content, not a summary of it."},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1772317800000,"lastRunAtMs":1772231400008,"lastStatus":"ok","lastDurationMs":1,"consecutiveErrors":0,"lastRunStatus":"ok","lastDeliveryStatus":"not-requested"}},{"id":"44fb9d22-a77a-4de1-9c09-5edef483264e","agentId":"main","name":"weekly-para-curation","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1770180106367,"updatedAtMs":1771779606630,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 1 * * 1","tz":"Asia/Hong_Kong"},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"🗂️ WEEKLY PARA CURATION\n\nExecute the PARA curation script:\n\npython3 /data/workspace/scripts/para_curation.py 2>&1\n\nScript will:\n1. Scan shared project directories\n2. Archive files older than 1 year\n3. Log migration details\n4. Create a migration report\n\nCheck /data/workspace/logs/para_curation.log for details.\n\nDo NOT post to any channel; return plain text only.","model":"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5","timeoutSeconds":180},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1772384400000,"lastRunAtMs":1771779600011,"lastStatus":"error","lastDurationMs":6619,"consecutiveErrors":1,"lastError":"cron announce delivery failed"},"delivery":{"mode":"announce","channel":"discord","to":"channel:1468164160398557216"}},{"id":"f17da2d2-3b49-4be5-be9d-d29a27a8dbb9","agentId":"main","name":"healthcheck:security-audit","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1770299752473,"updatedAtMs":1771786834028,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 3 * * 1","tz":"Asia/Hong_Kong"},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"next-heartbeat","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"Run a security audit: execute `openclaw security audit --deep` and `openclaw update status`. Compare results against the last audit. If any NEW findings appear (not previously accepted risks), return them clearly. Save results to memory/security-audit-latest.md. Accepted risks: dangerouslyDisableDeviceAuth=true, Sonnet 4 weak tier warning, Discord allowlist warning.\n\nDo NOT post to any channel; return plain text only. The delivery system handles routing.","model":"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5","timeoutSeconds":180},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1772391600000,"lastRunAtMs":1771786800011,"lastStatus":"error","lastDurationMs":34017,"consecutiveErrors":1,"lastError":"cron announce delivery failed"},"delivery":{"mode":"announce","channel":"discord","to":"channel:1468164160398557216"}},{"id":"3db9477e-5dee-4731-bfb4-9e0abfcbcab2","agentId":"main","name":"Weekly Memory Health Check","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1771334751465,"updatedAtMs":1771817394142,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 10 * * 1","tz":"Asia/Hong_Kong"},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"Weekly memory health check. Return plain text only.\n\n1. Check the builtin memory index at /data/.openclaw/memory/main.sqlite: total files, vault files (path LIKE \"memory/vault/%\"), squad files (path LIKE \"memory/squad/%\"), total chunks, total embeddings.\n\n2. Canary test with RETRY — run memory_search for \"Guillermo\" (high-confidence query). If it returns 0 results, wait 10 seconds and retry with \"TMNT fleet\". Only report FAIL if BOTH attempts return 0 results. If first fails but second succeeds, report WARN (transient).\n\n3. Check disk usage: du -sh /data/workspace/memory/ and du -sh /data/.openclaw/memory/\n\n4. Confirm QMD is NOT installed (we removed it Feb 23, now using OpenAI embeddings). Flag if /usr/local/bin/qmd exists.\n\n5. Report summary: index counts, canary pass/warn/fail, disk usage, backend type.\n\nSeverity guide:\n- Both canary queries fail = HIGH (search broken)\n- First fails, retry succeeds = WARN (transient)\n- Both succeed = OK","model":"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5","timeoutSeconds":120},"delivery":{"mode":"announce","to":"channel:1468164160398557216","bestEffort":true},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1772416800000,"lastRunAtMs":1771817380776,"lastStatus":"ok","lastDurationMs":13366,"consecutiveErrors":0}}],"total":11,"offset":0,"limit":11,"hasMore":false,"nextOffset":null},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772237273339}}
{"type":"message","id":"f914c5c6","parentId":"1fd9210e","timestamp":"2026-02-28T00:08:00.839Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see that the \"Molty Nightly Task Worker\" ran last at 1772215200015 (let me calculate: 1772215200015 ms / 1000 = 1772215200 seconds). Let me check the overnight log to see what happened.\n\nActually, the nightly task worker ran and `lastStatus: \"ok\"` and `lastDelivered: true`. So it did run. Let me check what the log says.\n\nThe cron ran at lastRunAtMs: 1772215200015. Let me convert: 1772215200 seconds. That's Feb 27 2026 18:00 UTC = Feb 28 02:00 HKT. So it ran overnight. And status is ok with delivery delivered.\n \nAh, I see the issue now—Guillermo's asking about the overnight update, but the delivery went to the \"last\" channel instead of #squad-updates. Let me look at the overnight log to understand what actually got delivered.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_01R1MapCw69bpomzWvbMFDVj","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls /data/workspace/logs/ | grep overnight | tail -5 && cat /data/workspace/logs/overnight-tasks-2026-02-27.md 2>/dev/null || echo \"not found\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":1,"output":340,"cacheRead":38648,"cacheWrite":6736,"totalTokens":45725,"cost":{"input":0.000003,"output":0.0051,"cacheRead":0.0115944,"cacheWrite":0.02526,"total":0.041957400000000006}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772237273349}}
{"type":"message","id":"984416fe","parentId":"f914c5c6","timestamp":"2026-02-28T00:08:00.873Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_01R1MapCw69bpomzWvbMFDVj","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"overnight-tasks-2026-02-25.md\novernight-tasks-2026-02-26.md\novernight-tasks-2026-02-27.md\novernight-tasks-2026-02-28.md\n# Overnight Tasks — 2026-02-27\n\n## ✅ Completed (1)\n- **Fix Discord read access for Molty** → [Notion: 🔍 Discord Read Access Investigation — Feb 27 2026](https://www.notion.so/Discord-Read-Access-Investigation-Feb-27-2026-31339dd69afd81d185ebd881f9ee3734)\n\n## ⏭️ Flagged — needs input (0)\n\n## ❌ Failed (0)\n\n---\n\n## Investigation Summary\n\n**Task:** Fix Discord read access for Molty (message tool action enum restricted to send only)\n\n**Root Cause Found:** The message tool action enum is **dynamically scoped to the current session channel** at startup. When Molty runs from Telegram (cron/overnight sessions), `resolveMessageToolSchemaActions()` calls `listChannelSupportedActions({ channel: \"telegram\" })` — which only returns Telegram actions. Discord actions (`read`, `search`) are never added to the enum.\n\n- **Config is fine:** `channels.discord.actions.messages=true` and `search=true` are both set correctly in `/data/.openclaw/openclaw.json`\n- **The scoping is intentional:** Code in `src/agents/tools/message-tool.ts` explicitly scopes to `currentChannelProvider` when present\n\n**Key files:**\n- `src/agents/tools/message-tool.ts` → `resolveMessageToolSchemaActions()` (line ~448)\n- `src/channels/plugins/actions/discord.ts` → `discordMessageActions.listActions()`\n- `src/channels/plugins/actions/telegram.ts` → Telegram's `listActions()`\n\n**Recommended fix options:**\n1. **Use Discord-bound sessions** for Discord read tasks (no code change needed — works today from #command-center)\n2. **Spawn Discord sub-agent** from cron when Discord reads are needed\n3. **OpenClaw feature request:** `tools.message.includeAllChannelActions: true` config to bypass per-channel scoping"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":13,"aggregated":"overnight-tasks-2026-02-25.md\novernight-tasks-2026-02-26.md\novernight-tasks-2026-02-27.md\novernight-tasks-2026-02-28.md\n# Overnight Tasks — 2026-02-27\n\n## ✅ Completed (1)\n- **Fix Discord read access for Molty** → [Notion: 🔍 Discord Read Access Investigation — Feb 27 2026](https://www.notion.so/Discord-Read-Access-Investigation-Feb-27-2026-31339dd69afd81d185ebd881f9ee3734)\n\n## ⏭️ Flagged — needs input (0)\n\n## ❌ Failed (0)\n\n---\n\n## Investigation Summary\n\n**Task:** Fix Discord read access for Molty (message tool action enum restricted to send only)\n\n**Root Cause Found:** The message tool action enum is **dynamically scoped to the current session channel** at startup. When Molty runs from Telegram (cron/overnight sessions), `resolveMessageToolSchemaActions()` calls `listChannelSupportedActions({ channel: \"telegram\" })` — which only returns Telegram actions. Discord actions (`read`, `search`) are never added to the enum.\n\n- **Config is fine:** `channels.discord.actions.messages=true` and `search=true` are both set correctly in `/data/.openclaw/openclaw.json`\n- **The scoping is intentional:** Code in `src/agents/tools/message-tool.ts` explicitly scopes to `currentChannelProvider` when present\n\n**Key files:**\n- `src/agents/tools/message-tool.ts` → `resolveMessageToolSchemaActions()` (line ~448)\n- `src/channels/plugins/actions/discord.ts` → `discordMessageActions.listActions()`\n- `src/channels/plugins/actions/telegram.ts` → Telegram's `listActions()`\n\n**Recommended fix options:**\n1. **Use Discord-bound sessions** for Discord read tasks (no code change needed — works today from #command-center)\n2. **Spawn Discord sub-agent** from cron when Discord reads are needed\n3. **OpenClaw feature request:** `tools.message.includeAllChannelActions: true` config to bypass per-channel scoping","cwd":"/data/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772237280861}}
{"type":"message","id":"5d708167","parentId":"984416fe","timestamp":"2026-02-28T00:08:07.442Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So Molty's overnight ran at 02:00 HKT Feb 28 and completed 1 task (Discord read access investigation). But the delivery was set to \"last\" channel, not #squad-updates. So the update was delivered somewhere but not visible to Guillermo in #squad-updates. Let me check where it was delivered.\n\nAlso there's a Feb 28 log too. Let me check that.\n\nActually wait - the nightly task worker ran at lastRunAtMs: 1772215200015. Let me calculate: 1772215200 / 3600 / 24 = days from epoch. Actually let me just think about it - the cron is \"0 18 * * *\" UTC which is 02:00 HKT. \n\nThe next run is scheduled for 1772301600000, and the last run completed successfully but went to the \"last\" channel instead of #squad-updates where Guillermo expected to see it. Let me look at the Feb 28 overnight logs to understand what happened.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_01CoNrFQdLxpoxHydsmgtNDU","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /data/workspace/logs/overnight-tasks-2026-02-28.md 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":1,"output":361,"cacheRead":45384,"cacheWrite":897,"totalTokens":46643,"cost":{"input":0.000003,"output":0.0054150000000000005,"cacheRead":0.0136152,"cacheWrite":0.00336375,"total":0.02239695}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772237280873}}
{"type":"message","id":"d0c98c18","parentId":"5d708167","timestamp":"2026-02-28T00:08:07.502Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_01CoNrFQdLxpoxHydsmgtNDU","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Overnight Tasks — 2026-02-28\n\n## ✅ Completed (3)\n\n- **🇪🇸 Spanish passport renewal — Guillermo + Memo** → [Notion: HK Consulate Guide](https://www.notion.so/Spanish-Passport-Renewal-Guillermo-Memo-HK-Consulate-Guide-31439dd69afd81399a4dc4a2887e7a81)\n  - Consulate address, phone, hours; full document checklist for adult renewal + minor first passport; action steps. **URGENT: Call Mon morning +852 2525 3041.**\n\n- **🇬🇧 British passport for Memo — first application guide** → [Notion: British Passport Guide](https://www.notion.so/British-Passport-for-Memo-First-Application-Guide-Born-Abroad-31439dd69afd810b9987e826f6336b3d)\n  - Eligibility check (Stephanie must hold British citizenship), full document list, online application flow from HK, fee (£86), 10-week processing warning. **Apply immediately.**\n\n- **🚀 Cyberport incubation/accelerator research for Cerebro** → [Notion: Cyberport Research](https://www.notion.so/Cyberport-Incubation-Accelerator-Cerebro-Eligibility-Research-31439dd69afd8147b803e0f8ef075191)\n  - CIP (HKD 500K, 24-month, open year-round), CCMF (entry-level pathway), CASP (requires incubatee status). Cerebro likely eligible if HK incorporated. Recommended path included.\n\n## ⏭️ Flagged — needs input (5)\n\n- **⌚ Build Whoop Health Integration**: Needs Guillermo's Whoop API credentials + account access. Cannot proceed without.\n\n- **Molty helps me launch Polymarket bot**: Ambiguous — \"launch\" could mean deploy, configure, or actively run. Needs Guillermo to clarify scope and share the bot code/location.\n\n- **🔴 Fill Brinc Deep Dive Q&A for Raphael**: Requires Guillermo to provide answers about Brinc. Raphael-facing task, cannot fabricate responses.\n\n- **Cerebro Feature — CRM and reminder to touch base with top contacts**: Feature design task requiring Guillermo's input on priorities and contact list. Flagged for Leonardo + Guillermo alignment.\n\n- **Cerebro — think of marketing strategy**: Strategic task requiring Guillermo's direction. Flagging for daytime working session — not appropriate to auto-draft without context.\n\n## ❌ Failed (0)\n\n---\n\n*Run by Molty 🦎 at 02:00 HKT, 28 Feb 2026. Molty's Den project was empty — executed highest-priority actionable tasks from Personal + Cerebro + Brinc projects.*"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":17,"aggregated":"# Overnight Tasks — 2026-02-28\n\n## ✅ Completed (3)\n\n- **🇪🇸 Spanish passport renewal — Guillermo + Memo** → [Notion: HK Consulate Guide](https://www.notion.so/Spanish-Passport-Renewal-Guillermo-Memo-HK-Consulate-Guide-31439dd69afd81399a4dc4a2887e7a81)\n  - Consulate address, phone, hours; full document checklist for adult renewal + minor first passport; action steps. **URGENT: Call Mon morning +852 2525 3041.**\n\n- **🇬🇧 British passport for Memo — first application guide** → [Notion: British Passport Guide](https://www.notion.so/British-Passport-for-Memo-First-Application-Guide-Born-Abroad-31439dd69afd810b9987e826f6336b3d)\n  - Eligibility check (Stephanie must hold British citizenship), full document list, online application flow from HK, fee (£86), 10-week processing warning. **Apply immediately.**\n\n- **🚀 Cyberport incubation/accelerator research for Cerebro** → [Notion: Cyberport Research](https://www.notion.so/Cyberport-Incubation-Accelerator-Cerebro-Eligibility-Research-31439dd69afd8147b803e0f8ef075191)\n  - CIP (HKD 500K, 24-month, open year-round), CCMF (entry-level pathway), CASP (requires incubatee status). Cerebro likely eligible if HK incorporated. Recommended path included.\n\n## ⏭️ Flagged — needs input (5)\n\n- **⌚ Build Whoop Health Integration**: Needs Guillermo's Whoop API credentials + account access. Cannot proceed without.\n\n- **Molty helps me launch Polymarket bot**: Ambi