{"type":"message","id":"69b45974","parentId":"f1eafbbe","timestamp":"2026-03-02T13:20:07.737Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The Railway token is not authorized at all - \"Not Authorized\". So the Railway API token is expired or invalid. That explains the 403. \n\nThe Dockerfile HAS been updated to v2026.3.1 on GitHub. If the Railway services are connected to that GitHub repo and have auto-deploy enabled, they might auto-deploy. But if not, Guillermo needs to manually trigger redeployments in Railway.\n\nLet me report this clearly in #squad-updates.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_01Xt4A2z5oPKQkYb9cGfgqqj","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","channel":"discord","target":"1468164181155909743","message":"⚠️ **Fleet Update v2026.3.1 — Manual Redeploy Needed**\n\nv2026.3.1 has 13 security patches and is critical. The Dockerfile on GitHub has been updated (`OPENCLAW_GIT_REF=v2026.3.1`) ✅ — but our Railway API token is returning Not Authorized, so automatic redeployments couldn't be triggered.\n\n**All 3 agents still on v2026.2.26 and need a manual Railway redeploy:**\n\n- 🦎 Molty — `ggvmolt` service\n- 🔴 Raphael — `ggv-raphael` service  \n- 🔵 Leonardo — `leonardo-production` service\n\n**Action for Guillermo:** Trigger a redeploy for each service in Railway (Deploy → Redeploy). Once they come back up they'll clone v2026.3.1 automatically from the updated Dockerfile.\n\nAlso flagging: the Railway API token (`1d318b62...`) needs to be refreshed — it's returning Not Authorized on all calls. This blocks automated fleet updates going forward."}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":1,"output":495,"cacheRead":71452,"cacheWrite":233,"totalTokens":72181,"cost":{"input":0.000003,"output":0.007425,"cacheRead":0.0214356,"cacheWrite":0.0008737500000000001,"total":0.02973735}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772457596885}}
