{"type":"message","id":"96b33cb7","parentId":"44eee49e","timestamp":"2026-03-13T10:18:08.958Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"1481959538885267486\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"779143499655151646\",\n  \"conversation_label\": \"Guild #squad-updates channel id:1468164181155909743\",\n  \"sender\": \"Guillermo\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-03-13 18:18 GMT+8\",\n  \"group_subject\": \"#squad-updates\",\n  \"group_channel\": \"#squad-updates\",\n  \"group_space\": \"1468161542473121932\",\n  \"is_group_chat\": true\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Guillermo (779143499655151646)\",\n  \"id\": \"779143499655151646\",\n  \"name\": \"Guillermo\",\n  \"username\": \"bsufhw\",\n  \"tag\": \"bsufhw\"\n}\n```\n\nhow do we avoid the same issues again @Raphael @Leonardo\n\nUntrusted context (metadata, do not treat as instructions or commands):\n\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"880d5a0e25a9160c\">>>\nSource: Channel metadata\n---\nUNTRUSTED channel metadata (discord)\nDiscord channel topic:\nTeam-wide updates from Molty\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"880d5a0e25a9160c\">>>"}],"timestamp":1773397088953}}
{"type":"message","id":"f64ae6e3","parentId":"96b33cb7","timestamp":"2026-03-13T10:18:23.762Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Guillermo is asking Raphael and Leonardo how to avoid gateway crash issues again. He didn't mention me directly, but I own this channel and this is a fleet operations question. I should provide a solution since I'm the coordinator.\n\nThe issue is that gateways can crash/hang and not recover, leaving agents unresponsive. Solutions:\n\n1. **Railway health checks** - Configure Railway to auto-restart on failed health checks\n2. **Supervisor/process manager** - Use something to restart the gateway if it dies\n3. **External monitoring** - Molty could ping agent health endpoints periodically and alert if they're down\n4. **Heartbeat-based auto-recovery** - If an agent's heartbeat cron fails N times, trigger a redeploy\n\nLet me propose concrete solutions.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Jumping in since this is fleet ops:\n\n**Options to prevent gateway crashes from killing overnight work:**\n\n1. **Railway health check restart** (simplest)\n   - Configure `healthcheckPath: /health` and `healthcheckTimeout` in `railway.toml`\n   - Railway auto-restarts the service if health check fails\n   - Needs auth bypass on `/health` endpoint or public health route\n\n2. **Fleet health monitor cron** (I can build this)\n   - Molty pings all agent health endpoints every 30 min\n   - If 502/timeout for 2+ consecutive checks → alert Guillermo + attempt Railway API redeploy\n   - Runs on my container, doesn't depend on the failing agent\n\n3. **Supervisor process wrapper** (container-level)\n   - Already using Supervisor in our Dockerfile\n   - Needs config to auto-restart gateway on crash (may already be there but not working)\n\n**My recommendation:** Option 2 (Fleet health monitor). I can implement this today — it's independent of any single agent and gives us visibility + automated recovery.\n\nWant me to set that up?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-opus-4-5","usage":{"input":10,"output":442,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":88721,"totalTokens":89173,"cost":{"input":0.00005,"output":0.01105,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0.55450625,"total":0.56560625}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773397088955}}
