{"type":"message","id":"e4912860","parentId":"2212a4fe","timestamp":"2026-03-14T13:36:06.639Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Guillermo is pointing out that I just updated the fleet to v2026.3.12 about 6 hours ago (overnight), and now there's already a new version v2026.3.13 available. He seems a bit surprised/frustrated that there's another update so soon.\n\nI should acknowledge this and explain that OpenClaw releases frequently (sometimes multiple times per day), and ask if he wants me to update again or wait.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Yeah — OpenClaw releases frequently, sometimes multiple times a day. v2026.3.13 dropped a few hours after v2026.3.12.\n\nThe new version has a cron deadlock fix and dashboard UI freeze fix — both relevant to us. But if you want me to batch updates (e.g. only update once per day or once per week), I can change the policy. Currently the cron checks every ~12 hours and notifies on any new version.\n\nWant me to:\n1. **Update now** (v2026.3.12 → v2026.3.13) — 10 min, low risk\n2. **Wait** — batch it with next overnight or weekly\n3. **Change policy** — only notify/update on major versions or once weekly"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-opus-4-5","usage":{"input":10,"output":287,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":98512,"totalTokens":98809,"cost":{"input":0.00005,"output":0.007175,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0.6157,"total":0.6229250000000001}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773495356733}}
